'''Reciprocal apprenticeship''' was a form of mutual [[Padawan/Legends|apprenticeship]] between [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]]. A facet of the [[Concordance of Fealty]],<ref name="DFS">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20050407a|series=The Dark Forces Saga|text=Part 1}}</ref> a ceremonial expression of trust by the exchange of the [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]] of two Jedi,<ref name="Skye">''[[SkyeWalkers: A Clone Wars Story]]''</ref> it had become rarely-practiced following the [[Cleansing of the Nine Houses]]<ref name="DFS" /> in the [[Old Sith Wars]] conflicts.<ref name="HotM">{{InsiderCite|80|The History of the Mandalorians: Exploring the Evolution of a Mighty Race of Warriors}}</ref>

To complete [[Gender/Legends|her]] [[Jedi training/Legends|training]] in [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] after abandoning its [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]], the former [[Emperor's Hand/Legends|Emperor's Hand]] [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] sought out [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Kyle Katarn]] and undertook a reciprocal apprenticeship with him, creating a bond between the two that allowed Jade to [[Mission to Dromund Kaas (New Republic)|redeem]] Katarn from the dark side of the Force<ref name="DFS" /> in [[10 ABY/Legends|10 ABY]].<ref name="Date">The events of ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Mysteries of the Sith]]'', including the [[Mission to Dromund Kaas (New Republic)|mission to Dromund Kaas]], take place five [[Standard year/Legends|years]] after those of ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Dark Forces II]]'', which ''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates to [[5 ABY/Legends|5 ABY]], five years before [[10 ABY/Legends|10 ABY]].</ref>

